Comedian Woli Arole has provided justification for his reaction upon seeing Grammy award-winning Wizkid. The comic act, who had a successful show tagged ‘Arole Revelation’ at Eko Hotels and Suites over the weekend shared a video where he bumped into the “Made in Lagos” global hitmaker. Arole made sure to bow for Big Wiz as he expressed delightful shock at seeing him. This made some persons question the action of the comedian who in turn reminded them that he bowed to the grace upon the singer’s life.   Skitmaker Lasisi Elenu loses mum     Davido employs Morgan Freeman for O2 Arena commercial     Kunle Afolayan working on another project featuring daughter   According to the father of one, a person attracts what they honour adding, it’s a great honour to be known and recognised by Machala himself. He tweeted: “Someone said Arole you BOWED when you saw “WIZKID”. I replied “Life is not about AGE but it’s about GRACE”. What you honor is what you “ATTRACT”. “It’s an honor for WIZKID to KNOW ME. Talkless of even knowing about my show #AroledRevelation. I celebrate GLORY.”